title: thread 'rustc' panicked at 'no entry found for key', compiler/rustc_metadata/src/rmeta/decoder/cstore_impl.rs:547:9

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code This happens on bjorn3@b18b50c800f3d1756bce9a62f849091743a50fbf. By performing the following steps: 1. Put the following in `config.toml`: ```toml profile = "compiler" changelog-seen = 2 [build] compiler-docs = false [rust] codegen-backends = ["llvm", "cranelift"] parallel-compiler = true ``` 2. Build using `./x.py build compiler/rustc_codegen_cranelift`. 3. Remove the `parallel-compiler = true` line. 4. Build again using `./x.py build compiler/rustc_codegen_cranelift`. ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: N/A ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'no entry found for key', compiler/rustc_metadata/src/rmeta/decoder/cstore_impl.rs:547:9 ``` and ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'Illegal read of: 77114', /rustc/0f231250ba7fe3a3f98a18aee9abfd65b104fb92/compiler/rustc_query_system/src/dep_graph/graph.rs:436:25 ```
